  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Rear hub bearing unit removal and installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Hub Bearing Unit Development"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "671_3.0_jpn_11581791_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Lift Set",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "G000319",
          "label": "Lift Set",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Rear wheel removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000659",
          "label": "Rear wheel removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Parking brake release"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Brake drum removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000695",
          "label": "Brake drum removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Remove rear wheel sensor clip and wire guide rubber"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "671_3.0_jpn_11581792_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the rear wheel sensor clip (A) and wire guide rubber (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "6. Hub bearing unit removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "671_3.0_jpn_11581793_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the hub bearing unit (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Since the rear wheel sensor is directly attached to the back of the hub bearing unit, be very careful not to damage the rear wheel sensor cord when removing the hub bearing unit.",
        "When installing, replace the mounting bolts (B) of the hub bearing unit with new ones."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "7. Rear wheel sensor removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "671_3.0_jpn_11581794_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the rear wheel sensor (B) from the hub bearing unit (A). Do not disconnect the wheel sensor cord."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "8. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "9. Wheel alignment Inspection and adjustment",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000655",
          "label": "Wheel alignment Inspection and adjustment",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "10. VSA sensor Midpoint write",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000714",
          "label": "VSA sensor Midpoint write",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
